<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,261,1556]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1493,1519]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<emphasis box="[610,680,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">lorica</emphasis>
, a Latin adjective meaning armour mostly made from leather, refers to the color and structure of the elytra that reminds of leather.
</paragraph>
